When I think about our friendship and how much it’s grown, I can’t help but think back to the hardest year of my life. You were there when my dad passed and when my dog died. That year was rough, and I even lost a lot of friends because I couldn’t be myself. I couldn’t be happy. But you? You stuck around. You came through for me, even when you didn’t have to. I’ll never be able to fully express how much that meant to me. You were a constant when everything felt like it was falling apart.

I remember that time at your party when everyone was shouting “Fuck you, dad” Without even thinking, I said it too. And then it hit me, my dad’s gone. But I laughed so hard, and you got it. You understood why I laughed. You knew it wasn’t just about the words. It was about finding a way to deal with the pain and still laugh about it also our dads are assholes right.... death don't absolve shit. That meant a lot to me... we just the same type of broken because of our narcissistic dads.

One thing I really admire about you is the way you’ve learned to trust yourself, especially when it comes to your art. You’re brave, and you express yourself so openly. You’ve built this confidence that I really aspire to have in my own life. I want to be able to trust my abilities the way you do, and I hope I can get there one day.

We’re Both Fucked Up, But At Least We’re Not Alone

I love our conversations about art and science. Every time we talk, I feel like I’m learning something new. It’s not just about the knowledge, though. It’s about the way you open up my world. You introduce me to so many great people, and that’s something I really value. Meeting the people you love has been so eye-opening because they’re just as good as you are. And that’s why I value our friendship so much. You’ve shown me a new way of looking at things, and I hope you keep bringing these amazing people into my life.

I think one of the reasons we connect so well is because we share the same dark sense of humor. We laugh at the mess of life more than we take it seriously, and it helps us both deal with everything that comes our way. Honestly, I feel like I’ve opened up to you more than anyone else, all while laughing about how messed up life can be.

Anyway, I guess what I’m saying is you’re kind of like my favorite emotional support person without the official therapy license. But hey, at least you’re not charging me by the hour :P Let’s keep surviving, thriving, and laughing at how ridiculous everything is because we both know life is a joke, and we’re just in on it and not like we can die together, or can we?

I really hope I bring the light into your life like you have..... I am always here for you, promise!


Love 
Mojo Jojo :*`
